Project 10: Job Portal System â€“ Project Report

1. Title: Job Portal System

2. Objective :

Develop a full-stack job portal system backend to manage users, jobs, and applications, demonstrating skills in Spring Boot, MySQL, and REST API design.

3. Technologies Used:

- Java 24
- Spring Boot 3.4.x
- Maven
- MySQL Database
- Spring Data JPA
- Postman (API testing)

4. Features / Functionality:

- User registration and login
- Post new jobs (admin)
- List all jobs
- Apply to a job
- Track applications by user

5. Architecture Diagram:

[Client / Postman] --> [Spring Boot Controller] --> [Service Layer] --> [JPA Repository] --> [MySQL Database]


6. Sample API Endpoints:

Endpoint	Method	Description

- /api/users	POST	Register a new user
- /api/jobs	POST	Post a new job
- /api/jobs	GET	List all jobs
- /api/apply	POST	Apply for a job

7. Sample JSON Payload (POST /api/jobs):

{
  "title": "Software Developer",
  "description": "Develop and maintain Java applications",
  "location": "Remote",
  "salary": 60000
}


8. Screenshots / Testing:

All Screenshots are available in the respective folders

9. Learning Outcomes:

- REST API development using Spring Boot
- Handling CRUD operations in MySQL
- Understanding relationships (user-job-application)
- Testing APIs using Postman